::Kaiser::
       He turns to face her and glares darkly.  "By killing anyone who 
disagreed.  I was successful because I don't waste resources.  It will take 
two bots to eliminate Hydras.  I think Tyrael and the Dragoon are our best 
choices.  Call it a hunch.  Either way, your job is to follow orders, not to 
be bitter that they were chosen for the prestigious assignment over you."

       He continues to glare taking a step toward Synergy, a fierce 
determination glowing in his eyes.  "Frankly, I know they aren't the best 
warriors here, I am.  But they should suffice for Hydras.  The rest of the 
battle will be equally intense, I assure you.  Although their exact numbers 
are unknown to me at this time, I am quite certain they will outnumber us.  
That means you may well have to fend off two bots on your own, unless of 
course, you don't think you can handle it."  He finally turns his dark eyes 
back to Tyrael awaiting his analysis.

--part1_162.205634eb.2bf3e1b6_boundary
